    <text>
        <body>       
                                

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>The<lb/>
                Rossmore Hotel<lb/>
                WABASH AVE NEAR 18TH ST.<lb/>
                Chicago USA.<lb/></p>
            <p>200 ROOMS AMERICAN PLAN&#44;<lb/>
                HAUK &#38; LEE<lb/>
                PROPRIETORS.<lb/>
                Chicago Ills. Jan 22nd 94<lb/></p>
            <p>My Dear Father.<lb/></p>
            <p>Your letter was received this mor&#45;<lb/>ning and I was surprised to read that I was to<lb/> go to Minneapolis&#44; and tho there is no need to tell you<lb/> that my heart is heavy at the thought of doing<lb/> such a thing yet I go to begin a new life and I feel<lb/> that I am under obligations which I will<lb/> <hi rend="underline">never</hi> be able to repay.<lb/></p>
            <p>As I said before it is<lb/> hard&#44; <hi rend="underline">very hard</hi> to believe a person like I have<lb/> been&#44; but before Him who sees us all I swear<lb/> to you that I shall do what is right before God<lb/> and man and make amends for the dreadful<lb/> past six months&#44; tho&#39; it will take me <hi rend="underline">many</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">many</hi> years&#41; as soon as I reach Minneapolis<lb/> I shall seek a situation and go to work honorably.<lb/></p>
            <p>What money you advance for<lb/> me as I said before I shall repay&#44; and believe<lb/> me that I care not for money either I seek<lb/> for nothing if anybody&#44; and all I look for<lb/> now is a reestablishment of my good<lb/> name which I once did credit to in Kansas<lb/> City.<lb/></p>
            <p>God knows I sometimes think that I<lb/> must have been crazy for I threw money<lb/> into gambling houses&#44; while I knew as soon as I<lb/> entered them that all I had would go.<lb/></p>
            <p>Believe ere we just once<lb/> more my dear Father and God knows you<lb/> will have no cause to regret it.<lb/></p>
            <p>Lay your head down at<lb/> night with the satisfaction that tho&#39; I<lb/> have been all that is bad and infamous&#44;<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>yet I have reformed and am now making<lb/> amends.</p>
            <p>I go to Minneapolis as soon as<lb/> my ticket arrives where I start in again<lb/> with the help of God in whom I put my<lb/> trust.<lb/>  Your son&#44;<lb/> Leon<lb/></p>
            </body>
